fields.content: London is the capital and largest city of the United Kingdom, standing on the River Thames in southeast England.
Tokyo is the capital of Japan and one of the most populous metropolitan areas in the world.
Canberra is the capital city of Australia, located inland and known for its national monuments.
Rome, the capital of Italy, is home to ancient ruins such as the Roman Forum and the Colosseum.
Moscow is the capital city of Russia and is known for its historic Red Square and the Kremlin.
Beijing, the capital of China, is known for its modern architecture as well as historical sites such as the Forbidden City.
Nairobi is the capital of Kenya, famous for its National Park and as a hub for safari tourism.
Washington, D.C. is the capital city of the United States, known for its monuments and museums.
Rio de Janeiro is a major city in Brazil, known for its Copacabana beaches and the Christ the Redeemer statue.
Oslo is the capital of Norway, known for its green spaces and museums such as the Viking Ship Museum.
Cows have best friends and get stressed when they are separated.
Bananas are berries, but strawberries are not.
Octopuses have three hearts and their blood is blue.
Honey never spoils. Archaeologists have found pots of honey in ancient Egyptian tombs that are over 3,000 years old.
Berne is the de facto capital of Switzerland, known for its medieval old town and Zytglogge clock tower.
Cape Town is a legislative capital of South Africa, renowned for its harbor and Table Mountain.
Abu Dhabi is the capital of the United Arab Emirates, known for its modern skyline and cultural landmarks.
Jakarta is the capital of Indonesia, known for its bustling metropolitan lifestyle.
Sharks existed before trees; they have been around for over 400 million years.
A group of flamingos is called a 'flamboyance'.
Helsinki is the capital city of Finland, located on the shore of the Gulf of Finland.
